Outpatients, visitors and staff will be offered the chance to get a flavour of the inpatient menu at Hairmyres Hospital.A patient meal tasting session has been arranged in the main atrium from noon until 2pm in the main atrium on Wednesday May 27.Sharon Murray, senior nurse and nutrition lead for Hairmyres Hospital, said: &quot;We are extremely proud of the food we provide for our patients and continually work with our service providers, dietitians and patient representatives to monitor nutritional standards, quality and patient satisfaction.&quot;We want to give patients, visitors and relatives a chance to sample the food that is being served in the wards on the same day and to give us their views.&quot;